title: 'I am not taking drugs!': Musk refutes claims of drug abuse during 2024 campaign trail
description: Elon Musk refuted claims of extensive drug use, including ketamine, during the 2024 Presidential campaign, labeling a New York Times report as false. He admitted to a past prescription for ketamine to combat mental health issues but stated he hasn't used it recently. The report alleged Musk's drug use led to health problems and cited erratic behavior.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Snub to Elon Musk? Donald Trump drops Nasa pick Jared Isaacman, over alleged ties with democrats
description: Donald Trump has withdrawn Jared Isaacman's nomination for Nasa administrator just before the senate confirmation vote. Isaacman, the CEO of Shift4 and a SpaceX mission participant, was nominated in December. He distanced himself from Elon Musk's views on lunar landings during his confirmation hearing, pledging to prioritize them if confirmed.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Women and girls ‘not safe anywhere’ as Darfur suffers surge in sexual violence
description: Médecins Sans Frontières report sparks calls for Sudan’s warring parties to be held to account for rapes and attacks As Sudan’s Darfur region has been overrun by militias, women are facing the constant threat of sexual violence, Médecins Sans Frontières (MSF) has reported.The medical charity said in the South Darfur region alone its workers treated 659 sexual violence survivors between January and March this year, more than two-thirds of whom had been raped. title: At least 115 killed in floods in central Nigeria
description: Several people remain missing in state of Niger after torrential rains submerged town of MokwaMore than 100 people have died and several others remain missing after a torrential downpour in the central Nigerian state of Niger, local authorities said on Friday.Floods submerged the town of Mokwa after the rains began on Wednesday night and continued into Thursday morning. Ibrahim Audu Hussein, a spokesperson for the state emergency management agency, said rescue efforts were still under way on Friday. Continue reading...
author: Eromo Egbejule in Abidjan with agencies
